Uni cars data story

To all the Car Geeks

I observed parked cars at various University of Auckland buildings - OGGB, Engineering faculty, Science faculty and General library. I recorded the brand, colour, origin, and where I saw them. This data will show approximately - what car brand (and origin for example japanese, german) is the most popular (I was pretty sure it will be toyota :D ) on campus

Most popular car brands

Alt-text: Horizontal bar chart showing which car brands were observed most on campus.

Toyota, as expected was the most popular brand on campus 😅 I guess it should be true not only in the city centre..

Car colour distribution by location

Alt-text: Grouped bar chart showing how car colours differ by building location.

Black and white were the most common colours overall, but Science and the General Library had a more balanced distribution with more grey/silver and blue cars (which were toyotas)

Car counts by brand type

Alt-text: Boxplot comparing number of cars seen per day for each brand origin (Japanese, German, etc.)

Japanese cars were the most frequently seen, with a wide range of daily counts. German brands were also common, but less frequent than Japanese brands.

Summary

In general I can say that the OGGB and Engineering roads featured more luxury cars and darker colours, the Science building and General Library had more variety.
